out of the labor force. Martin Feldstein, &quot;Unemployment Compensation:
 Its Effect on Unemployment,&quot; <I>Monthly Labor Review </I>
99 (March 1976), and &quot;The Effect of Temporary Unemployment
Insurance on Temporary Layoff Unemployment,&quot; <I>American
Economic Review</I> 68 (December 1978). A government study found
that every $1.00 of additional welfare lowered labor and earnings
among low&#173;income persons by $0.80. SRI International, <I>Final
