<TITLE>DR. JAMES PRZYSTUP -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>DR. JAMES PRZYSTUP</H3>
<B>DIRECTOR, ASIAN STUDIES CENTER</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/przystup.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Przystup, a specialist on Japan, is the Defense Department's former Director of Planning for Asia-Pacific security strategy (1991-94). He also served on the State Department's policy-planning staff (1987-91), as Deputy Director of the U.S. Presidential Commission on U.S.-Japan Relations, and as IBM's Manager for Governmental Programs for the Asia-Pacific region. Przystup earned his Ph.D. in diplomatic history and M.S. in international relations at the University of Chicago.

