<TITLE>Chapter 2</TITLE>     
<H2><CENTER><I><FONT SIZE="+3">C</FONT>hapter 2</H2></I></CENTER>     
<H3>Where We Have Been in Foreign Aid</H3>     
<HR SIZE=3>     
<P>     
Since 1946, the U.S. has spent some $450 billion in military and economic bilateral assistance to      
other countries.<FONT SIZE="-2">[1]</FONT>  Below is a breakdown of how the U.S. has distributed      
this vast sum.       
